word_mean_info__list.difference: 含贬义，指乌合之众、暴民。
与crowd含义很接近，常可换用，但侧重指向前运动的群众。
指群众或平民，在西方国家含贬义，在我国含褒义。
本义指一大群紧紧聚集在一起的人群，现指群众整体，由个体结合的人群或大众。
最普通用词，不带任何色彩，泛指不确定数量的人们。
常和动态动词连用，指“从……上面越过”或“横越”；表静态时，指“在彼处”。

指“从……的一边到另一边”，强调横过，多与动态动词连用。

bilingual.source: He wanted to get through the park quickly.

bilingual.target: 小路蜿蜒穿过陡峭的山丘。

bilingual.source: Moko just came flying through the water.
bilingual.target: 莫科只是飞快地穿过水面。

bilingual.source: It was only a short walk through the park.
bilingual.target: 这只是穿过公园的一小段路。

bilingual.source: In the north, a river runs through the city.
bilingual.target: 在北边，一条河流穿过城市。

bilingual.source: The express train went through a long tunnel.
bilingual.target: 快车穿过了一条长长的隧道。

bilingual.source: The children went through the gate into the castle.
bilingual.target: 孩子们穿过大门进入城堡。

list.abstract: through（英[θruː]，美[θruː]），英语单词，作介词为穿过；完成；下承式，作形容词为直达的；联运的；全程的。短语搭配有go through（经历）、get through（通过）、look through（浏览）。例句为“Sunlight passes down through the gases.（阳光穿过气体。）” through与crowd含义很接近，常可换用，但侧重指向前运动的群众。across指“从……的一边到另一边”，强调横过，多与动态动词连用。

yingyinNormal.en: Samantha, you go right through that door.
yingyinNormal.zh: 萨曼塔，就穿过那扇门。

yingyinNormal.en: The road didn't cut through the land like that interstate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 路并不像那条州际公路一样直接穿过沙漠

yingyinNormal.en: Underneath, through the ring, lock it off. Tighten. And pay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从下面穿过这个环，拉好，绑紧，然后付钱。

yingyinNormal.en: If you're trying to get to the Open Ocean exhibit go through the pipes. Through the pipes. Great.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想到大洋区展览馆只要穿过这水管就可以了。穿过水管？太好了。

yingyinNormal.en: And we knew you must have gotten out through the pipes. Through the pipes. That's right, sweetie. And so we did too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们知道你一定是穿过水管出去了。穿过水管。没错，所以我们也跟着出去。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh it's going through the door. It's going up the stairs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，它穿过了门！上了楼梯。

yingyinNormal.en: Through the pipes? Yep. Take two lefts, swim straight and you'll hit it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 穿过水管？对。左转两次，直直游就到了。

yingyinNormal.en: The only way to the internal mechanics was through solid titanium.
yingyinNormal.zh: 唯一能进入导弹内部结构的方法是穿过钛固体。

yingyinNormal.en: You're running out of time, which is why we must go through Mirkwood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们没多少时间了。所以我们必须穿过黑森林。

yingyinNormal.en: Didn't it look like that spear was going to go right through your skull? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那支长矛逼真得就像要直接穿过咱的头啊。才怪。

yingyinNormal.en: And this is what you need to use to actually get through this creek onto the Rio Negro.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们就是要坐着它，穿过这条河道进入里奥内格罗。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: My quest has taken me through the physical, the metaphysical, the delusional and back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的追求带领我穿过了物理，形而上学，幻觉又带了回来。

yingyinNormal.en: He walked through forests, then across mountains, across seas. And are you sleepy yet? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们走过了森林穿过大山走过大海。现在你觉得困了吗？不困！

yingyinNormal.en: Remember when we would track blood ox through the Frostwind dunes? There is always meat. Always life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还记得那是我们穿过霜风沙丘去捕杀血牛？总是有肉吃，蛊然生机。

yingyinNormal.en: What about the wall? 8 feet high. Cinder block. No way through it. You go over or under.
yingyinNormal.zh: 围墙呢？8英尺高的焦渣石，不可能穿过的，你只能从上面或者从下面绕过。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you know, this morning, I was on a train that went through a city that wouldn't exist if it wasn't for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道吗，今天早上，我在火车上，穿过一个你将不会存在的城市。

yingyinNormal.en: I just hope that when Hal get shot it's through the front of his jacket. Like a simple entry wound not what you miss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只希望哈尔中枪时，是穿过夹克前面。像个简单射伤，不足为虑。

yingyinNormal.en: How did the ship get through the mist? I thought nobody could but us. Unless nobody was on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这艘船是如何穿过迷雾的？我以为除了我们没人能做到，除非这艘船上没有人。

yingyinNormal.en: Is that the electrode? That is the electrode. So basically, there's a big electric current running through that thing?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是电极？是的，这就是电极从根本上说现在有电穿过这个东西？

yingyinNormal.en: Welcome to Hogwarts. Now, in the few moment, you'll pass through these doors and join your classmates.
yingyinNormal.zh: 欢迎来霍格沃茨。好了，再过一会儿，你们会穿过这些门和你们的同学在一起。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Through</highlight> a more diffuse "halo effect," whereby its good deeds earn it greater consideration from consumers and others.

examination_example.sentence: However, Obamacare has allowed more than 12 million people to either get insurance <highlight>through</highlight> Medicaid or the exchanges.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，奥巴马医改已经允许超过1200万人通过医疗补助或交易所获得保险。

examination_example.sentence: I believe it is precisely this permanent coexistence of metaphysical message <highlight>through</highlight> physical means that is the strength of music.

examination_example.sentence: This very fact embodied the new ways of thinking that swept <highlight>through</highlight> Europe during most of 17th century.

examination_example.sentence: You should be able to spot gaps in the tree line due to other paths people carve <highlight>through</highlight> the woods.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你应该能够发现由于人们在树林中开辟的其他道路而造成的树线间隙。

examination_example.sentence: Chomsky's grammar should show patterns of language change that are independent of the family tree or the pathway tracked <highlight>through</highlight> it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乔姆斯基的语法应展现语言变化的模式，这些模式不受语言谱系或贯穿其中的路径影响。

examination_example.sentence: It's almost impossible to go <highlight>through</highlight> life without experiencing some kind of failure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 度过一生而不经历某种失败几乎是不可能的。

examination_example.sentence: Sometimes it is easy to feel bad because you are going <highlight>through</highlight> tough times.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有时候很容易感觉不好，因为你正在经历艰难的时期。

examination_example.sentence: The court has ruled that police don't violate the Fourth Amendment when they go <highlight>through</highlight> the wallet or pocketbook of an arrestee without a warrant.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 法院裁定，警察在没有逮捕令的情况下检查被捕者的钱包或皮夹时，不违反第四修正案。

examination_example.sentence: Maybe you haven't finished thinking the problem <highlight>through</highlight>, or you want to get a clearer sense of what the group thinks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也许你还没有把问题从头到尾想清楚，或者你想更清楚地了解小组的想法。

examination_example.sentence: In many cases, it would not be overly burdensome for authorities to obtain a warrant to search <highlight>through</highlight> phone contents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在许多情况下，当局获得搜查令以搜查手机内容不会过于繁重。

examination_example.sentence: Carter sifted <highlight>through</highlight> rubble in the Valley of the Kings for seven years before he located the tomb in 1922.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Carter在“帝王谷”的瓦砾中筛选了七年，直到1922年他才找到这座坟墓。

examination_example.sentence: Carry their plans <highlight>through</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实施他们的计划。

examination_example.sentence: You will see that mental health has been there to direct you <highlight>through</highlight> all your difficult decisions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你会看到心理健康一直在那里指导你完成所有困难的决定。

examination_example.sentence: His biographies were held up as beacons to guide the working man <highlight>through</highlight> his difficult life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他写的传记被奉为指路明灯，指引这位劳动者度过艰难的一生。

examination_example.sentence: When women do break <highlight>through</highlight> to the summit of corporate power, they attract massive attention.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当女性真正突破到公司权力的顶峰时，她们会引起广泛的关注。

examination_example.sentence: They open the way to equality and they break <highlight>through</highlight> the glass ceiling.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们（这种做法）开辟了通往平等的道路，打破了玻璃天花板。

examination_example.sentence: Given their combined market value of more than $5.5 trillion, rifling <highlight>through</highlight> such small deals might seem beside the point.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 鉴于它们的总市值超过5.5万亿美元，快速审查这样的小规模交易可能看起来无关紧要。

examination_example.sentence: See <highlight>through</highlight> the glass ceiling.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 识破玻璃天花板（指女性在职务升迁上遇到的无形障碍)。

examination_example.sentence: To win over these young workers, manufacturers have to clear another major hurdle: parents, who lived <highlight>through</highlight> the worst US economic downturn.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要赢得这些年轻的工人，制造商必须清除另一个主要障碍：家长。他们经历了美国最严重的一次经济下行。

examination_example.sentence: Emphasize your team and how <highlight>through</highlight> their talents, your vision was realized.

examination_example.sentence: Researchers found <highlight>through</highlight> experiments that students could be taught to respond to stress in a more positive way.

examination_example.sentence: They can also harm other wild species <highlight>through</highlight> indirect competition, rather than eating them or shrinking their food supply.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们还可以通过间接竞争伤害其他野生物种，而不是吃掉它们或减少它们的食物供应。

examination_example.sentence: The body uses a lot of energy stores for growth and repair <highlight>through</highlight> the night.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 整个晚上，身体需要大量的能量储备用于生长和修复。

examination_example.sentence: We recently caught up with yoga entrepreneur Leah Zaccaria, who put herself <highlight>through</highlight> the fire of change to completely reinvent herself.
